				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Want to raise your beg skill? When on the boat between conintents target the ship and face the mast. Click beg and it'll act like you are begging an npc (In essence you are) but won't ever succeed plus you never get killed.<BR>
    There is also a way for enchanters and druids to kill the PoD, this is just for fun as you will not get faction nor loot. This works in Kelethin because the PoD is near where newbies hunt. Charm a bat and tell it to attack the PoD, the guards will come in and take him down (I did it twice) Do not kill your bat afterwards or the guards will stop hitting him and kill you.<BR>
Not enough? want another druid/enchanter trick? Use minor illusion or treeform right next to a wall, then walk into the wall as you turn it off, rinse and repeat and you'll walk through walls and doors!<BR>
Now I am getting old? Last trick, I think enchanters can do this, only tried with my druid. Cast treeform and levitate, then memorize whirling wind and blast yourself, you will raise into the air and not come down! This trick's only purpose is mutiple winds will get you high into the sky till you run out of bat wings or mana and fall to the ground below (Possibly for high dmg if you didn't take off treeform and start the descent) Thats it, mostly useless tips you DIDN'T KNOW ABOUT. Don't tell verant, they might fix this.
